        guidedScript: "This practice should follow genuine familiarity with Shambhavi Mahamudra and extended Kumbhaka. Begin with twenty minutes of pranayama to settle and charge the system. Then engage Shambhavi Mahamudra — the eyes turned up and in toward the third eye — while also engaging a full Kumbhaka, holding the breath after a complete inhale, and adding a gentle full-body squeeze, contracting the major muscle groups together as you hold. In this combined, charged stillness, imagine an internal flash of light — not violent, but sudden and total — moving through every cell simultaneously, like a single note struck once and allowed to resonate fully through the whole instrument of the body. Hold for as long as is genuinely comfortable, then release the muscles, the eyes, and the breath together, slowly, and rest in stillness afterward. The Siddhas called this Marma consciousness — the trained ability to direct concentrated prana to specific points of genetic expression through combined breath, gaze, and muscular engagement. Repeat this sequence three to five times across the sitting, resting fully between each round.",
